text: Glarus Nord is a municipality of the canton of Glarus in Switzerland. On 1 January 2011, the former municipalities of Bilten, Filzbach, Mollis, Mühlehorn, Näfels, Niederurnen, Oberurnen and Obstalden merged into the new municipality of Glarus Nord. Glarus Nord is one of three municipalities of the canton of Glarus, the others being Glarus and Glarus Süd. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website of Glarus Nord Category:Municipalities of Glarus Category:Cities in Switzerland Category:2011 establishments in Switzerland
